# {{ .ProjectName }}

Generated by `gos` using the `api-minimal` template.

## Quick start

```bash
go run ./cmd/api serve
go run ./cmd/api schedule
go run ./cmd/api queue
go test ./...
go build ./cmd/api
```

Health check:

```bash
curl http://127.0.0.1:8080/healthz
```

`go run ./cmd/api` defaults to `serve`. Commands are implemented with Cobra.

Add a Cobra command:

```bash
gos make:command sync-orders --register
go run ./cmd/api sync-orders
```

## Layout

```text
cmd/api                  API entrypoint
internal/command         CLI command scripts generated by gos
internal/config          environment configuration
internal/interfaces/http HTTP router and handlers
internal/logging         slog logger setup
internal/worker          scheduled job and queue worker lifecycle helpers
```

Configuration:

```text
APP_NAME
HTTP_ADDR
HTTP_READ_HEADER_TIMEOUT
HTTP_READ_TIMEOUT
HTTP_WRITE_TIMEOUT
HTTP_IDLE_TIMEOUT
HTTP_MAX_HEADER_BYTES
HTTP_MAX_BODY_BYTES
LOG_LEVEL
{{- if .WithOpenTelemetry }}
OTEL_ENABLED
OTEL_SERVICE_NAME
OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT
OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_INSECURE
{{- end }}
```

Logging is initialized from `internal/logging`. `LOG_LEVEL` supports `debug`, `info`, `warn`, `warning`, and `error`; logs are emitted as JSON to stdout.{{ if .WithOpenTelemetry }} When tracing is enabled, log records automatically include `trace_id` and `span_id` when the current context carries a valid span.{{ end }}

Boolean, integer, int64, and duration environment variables are parsed strictly. Invalid values such as `OTEL_ENABLED=maybe`, `HTTP_MAX_HEADER_BYTES=abc`, or `HTTP_READ_TIMEOUT=abc` fail during startup instead of silently falling back to defaults. `HTTP_MAX_BODY_BYTES=0` disables request body size limiting.
{{ if .WithOpenTelemetry }}
## Observability

OpenTelemetry tracing support is included but disabled by default.

```bash
OTEL_ENABLED=false
OTEL_SERVICE_NAME={{ .AppName }}
OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=localhost:4318
OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_INSECURE=true
```

When enabled, startup configures an OTLP HTTP trace exporter and wraps the HTTP router with `otelhttp`.
{{ end }}
